## 3. Add safe decode logic

Add this inside `Common`:

```csharp
private static bool TryDecodeCurrentSession(string? session, out string plainSession, out bool shouldRewriteCookie)
{
    plainSession = string.Empty;
    shouldRewriteCookie = false;

    if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(session))
    {
        return false;
    }

    try
    {
        // New current format: v3:Compress(plainSession)
        if (session.StartsWith(CurrentArchiveVersion))
        {
            string compressedPart = session.Substring(CurrentArchiveVersion.Length);
            plainSession = DecompressString(compressedPart);
            return true;
        }

        // Support your current unversioned compressed-only cookies temporarily.
        // These are not old encrypted cookies, but cookies created before adding v3:.
        plainSession = DecompressString(session);
        shouldRewriteCookie = true;
        return true;
    }
    catch
    {
        // Old encrypted cookies or corrupted cookies will arrive here.
        return false;
    }
}
```

This does 3 things:

```text
v3 compressed cookie       → accepted
unversioned compressed     → accepted, then rewritten as v3
old encrypted cookie       → rejected and deleted
corrupted cookie           → rejected and deleted
```

