## Important warning

Your current version is **compressed only**, not encrypted and not signed.

That means the cookie content is not truly protected. Since you store things like:

```text
Role
Activities
Company
Email
User
Exp
```

this is risky for authorization. At minimum, the cookie should be protected using ASP.NET Core Data Protection or signed to prevent tampering.

But for your immediate issue — safely removing old encrypted cookies and depending on the current compressed version — the code above will fix the crash.

## Final behavior after this change

```text
User has v3 cookie
→ app works normally

User has unversioned compressed cookie
→ app reads it and rewrites it as v3

User has old encrypted cookie
→ app deletes ArchiveData and treats user as logged out

User has corrupted cookie
→ app deletes ArchiveData and treats user as logged out
```

This prevents the `InvalidDataException` from breaking `_Layout.cshtml` and causing the VIP to show `502 Bad Gateway`.
